description:
File: rust/lichen-coap/src/codec.rs:453-460

Issue: The content_format() method creates a local array and slices it:
    let bytes = format.to_be_bytes();
    let value = match format {
        0 => &bytes[2..2],
        1..=0xFF => &bytes[1..2],
        _ => &bytes[0..2],
    };
    self.option(OptionNumber::ContentFormat as u16, value)

This is idiomatic Rust but could be slightly clearer. The bytes array lives long enough because the method call happens in the same expression.

Actually this is fine - the borrow checker ensures the slice is valid for the option() call. No issue here.

Closing as non-issue.
